Close Brace 5 Minute React: SublimeText

---------
Resources
---------

  ES6 for Everyone course - Wes Bos: https://es6.io/friend/CLOSEBRACE

  Arrow Functions: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Functions/Arrow_functions



---------
Commands
---------

  Node Version Manager (NVM): 

    Install version: $ nvm install v6.10.0

    View installed versions: $ nvm ls

    Set verions: $ nvm use v6.10.0  *Anytime you switch versions, you have to reinstall any global Node modules needed


  Node:

    Enter Node Console: $ Node

  Nodemon: 

    Launch: $ nodemon npm start

-------
Install
-------

  Install Homebrew:
    
    $ /usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
  
  Update Homebrew: 
    
    $ brew update

  Install or Update NVM (Node Version Manager):
    
    $ brew install nvm  
    - or -
    $ brew update nvm

    Add NVM to shell:

      $ cd ~
      $ mkdir $HOME/.nvm

      Add to end of bash file (.bash_profile -or- .zshrc): 

          export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
          . "/usr/local/opt/nvm/nvm.sh"

      Save & kill terminal session - then $ nvm

  Install Yarn (Package Control):

    $ brew update && brew install yarn

    edit shell config (.bash_profile or .zshrc)

      add to eof: export PATH="$PATH: yarn global bin"

  Install Nodemon (Node Monitor):

    $ yarn global add nodemon





-----
Yarn
-----
  
  Initialize a new package using Yarn:

    $ yarn init

    follow propmts > creates package.json in current folder

  Add packages dependencies:

    $ yarn add [package name] (ex. $ yarn add map-reverse)















